    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Long before settlers arrived, the Lenni Lenape people inhabited the land that is now North Middletown.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/north_middletown_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Middletown Township, the parent of North Middletown, was founded in 1664 as one of the first colonial seats under the Monmouth Patent.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/north_middletown_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The first Baptist congregation in New Jersey began in 1688 at Middletown, a milestone for the region.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://middletownnj.org/249/History"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "All Saints Memorial, an Episcopal church built in 1864 in nearby Navesink, earned National Historic Landmark status.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
